Good Morning!! Tomorrow we will be having a guest speaker on our live feed, James and Christina Post who are part of Wycliffe Bible Translators in Papua New Guinea (PNG) will be giving an update. As a church body we support the Post Family both financially and in prayer as they continue to work on Bible Translation in PNG. http://www.thepostsinpng.com/
follow the link to see more about their ministry.

We will also be sharing communion together in our morning service as regularly scheduled. If you would like to join us in remembering what Jesus Christ has done for us, please be prepared with a little juice and bread. The elements are not as important as the heart of worship and thanksgiving for what Jesus did for us.

post_text: Good morning!! Today begins week 9 in our Quiet Time. As I read about the different sacrifices that had to be made to cover sin I thank God for his plan to send Jesus, the perfect sacrifice, to die for all sin. Don‚Äôt take it for granted, be amazed that he loved us so much to die for us. Remain in a right relationship with God, humble yourself, confess your sin (agree with God) and be forgiven. Live like you are forgiven!!!
text: Good morning!! Today begins week 9 in our Quiet Time. Live like you are forgiven!!!

post_text: Week 6 begins today. Yesterday ended with Paul's confidence of his eternal view of life. "So we fix our eyes not on what is seen, but on what is unseen. For what is seen is temporary, but what is unseen is eternal!" What are your eyes fixed on? Your problems-they are temporary! Poor health - also temporary for we will get a new body when we rise with Christ.

I like the promise in today's reading, verse 14 says; Know also that wisdom is sweet to your soul; if you find it, there is a future hope for you, and your hope will not be cut off.

Our hope is in Jesus Christ and the wisdom of believing He is who He says He is, is sweet to our soul. No matter what trials we go through our hope in Jesus will give us a future and it will not be taken away from us. Our future is eternity in heaven!

Today's reading in 1 Chronicles sets up David as king and we rejoice with the Israelites as Jerusalem is restored. Yesterday we see king Saul died because he was unfaithful to The Lord; he no longer inquired of The Lord. Today we see the difference with king David in verse 9, David became more and more powerful because The Lord was with him. Let's make it a habit to inquire of The Lord as we go about our days.

post_text: The passage today in Daniel shows us how important it is to learn from the mistakes of others and the fact that God will not be mocked. Verse 23, Instead, you have set yourself up against The Lord of heaven. You had the goblets from his temple brought to you, and you and your nobles, your wives and your concubines drank wine from them. You praised the gods of silver and gold, bronze, iron, wood and stone which you cannot see or hear or understand. But you did not honor the God who holds in his hand your life and all your ways.
text: The passage today in Daniel shows us how important it is to learn from the mistakes of others and the fact that God will not be mocked. Verse 23, Instead, you have set yourself up against The Lord of heaven. You had the goblets from his temple brought to you, and you and your nobles, your wives and your concubines drank wine from them. You praised the gods of silver and gold, bronze, iron, wood and stone which you cannot see or hear or understand. But you did not honor the God who holds in his hand your life and all your ways.

post_text: Today we see the pride of king Nebuchadnezzar, the patience of our God and true humility. God gave the king one year to repent; patience. Verse 30 reeks of a kings pride (pride goes before the fall) the consequences come swiftly after, total humility. But what happens next is the most important, how do we respond to being humbled. Daniel 4:34, At the end of that time, I, Nebuchadnezzar, raised my eyes toward heaven, and my sanity was restored. Then I praised the Most High; I honored and glorified him who lives forever. His dominion is an eternal dominion; his kingdom endures from generation to generation.

post_text:
Daniel 4:27 "Therefore, O king, be pleased to accept my advise: Renounce your sins by doing what is right, and your wickedness by being kind to the oppressed. It may be that then your prosperity will continue."
Daniel relays the interpretation of the second dream which tells of how the king will be humiliated/crazy state of mind for seven years.
In this Daniel showed his love and concern to the king; his captor, enemy, a non-believer. Do we show the same concern for those God has put in our lives?

Daniel 4:2-3 It is my pleasure to tell you about the miraculous signs and wonders that the Most High God has performed for me. How great are his signs, how mighty his wonders! His kingdom is an eternal kingdom; his dominion endures from generation to generation.

Daniel 4:2-3 It is my pleasure to tell you about the miraculous signs and wonders that the Most High God has performed for me. How great are his signs, how mighty his wonders! His kingdom is an eternal kingdom; his dominion endures from generation to generation.

King Nebuchadnezzar had it right he understands who God is but he stopped short in his application to his own life. What will you do about God in your personal life for even the demons believe.

post_text:
Daniel 3:24-25, Then king Nebuchadnezzar leaped to his feet in amazement and asked his advisers, "weren't there three men that we tied up and threw into the fire?" They replied, "Certainly, O king." He said, "Look! I see four men walking around in the fire, unbound and unharmed, and the fourth looks like the son of the gods."

We need to be confident of this, when we are faced with the fiery trials in our life Jesus Christ is walking beside us all the time, protecting and comforting us. He is our Savior.

Today was the Parable of the prodigal son, so many good lessons for us in this one. But the one thing that always gets me is how the father never gave up hope, verse 20 where it says, But while he was still a long way off, his father saw him and was filled with compassion for him, he ran to his son, threw his arms around him and kissed him. This is how our heavenly Father is with us when we chose to go our own way, he never gives up hope and when we come to our senses, He is right there, filled with compassion and gathers us up in His loving arms. Let us run to the waiting arms of our heavenly Father never to stray again!!
